So when they met someone who matched culturally was knowledgable, they couldn't peg her. At the same time, they were shocked that one participant went to a Catholic school because it espoused similar values. I don't think there's anything wrong with seeing Islam as cultural more than spiritual, and I'm not here to judge people for how the practice. I just think that the media is set on portraying Islam as monolithic and victimizing us while also falling into negative stereotypes, and in a lot of ways the participants in this video proved them right by doing the same thing. While I understand stereotyping is kind of part of the strategy, the video was supposed to show that Muslims can be anyone and they proceeded to eliminate participants who didn't fit what they thought a Muslim was supposed to be.
